<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Ok I haven't played EQ for that long and have used my time playing LOTS of different characters. Some all the way up into the high teens, before I fell for the SK.<P>Anyway I spend most of my time exploring and stuff, but wanted, for a long time, to begin to explore the fields of trading.<P>So I collected 4 bags of stuff from the bank and travelled to the EC tunnel. Everything was going fine untill a DDD (Damn Dirty Dwarf) turned up. He wanted to see the bags and then proceded to commend me on my equipment and wanted to see it.<P>I showed him some in the trade window as he requested and the second it was full he cancelled the trade picked up the dropped stuff and logged. <P>I haven't seen my BP, Gauntlets or the 2 bags of words and runes he stole from me!!<P>I petitioned and had a long chat with a GM, but since I was going on vecation the next morning and just came back today I haven't herd much.<P>I was wondering if any of you guys and girls have had similar experiences. <P>I know some would say this is just the clever fooling the less clever. I offcourse (Big surprise) don't see it that way. <P>In a real trade you can't just run off with the merchandise and if you could (yes some places you can, dohh) the merchant would be able to pursue and or grap hold of the Thief when he was squading on the ground groping for your stuff.<P>Since that is not a possibility in EQ I might stand to loose the stuff for good. For a NON twink lvl 24 SK that sucks   <IMG SRC="eek.gif" border="0"> <P>I don't care much about the bags since it was only pp, but my BP (Bronze) and Gauntlets (AC 8 and +3 in str and agi) really hurts.<P>Anyway give me your thoughts on the subject....<P>Ohh the Dwarfs name was Duraf, but I suspect he was just a stoge character and have been deleated after transferring my equipment to another character (something that also dosen't sound right in the argumentation that this kind of behavior should be tolerated).
