<IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/profile.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Profile for Lumine-Jaz"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://" target=_new><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/homepage.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Author's Homepage"></A> &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=private_message&u=00000997"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/priv_message.gif" BORDER='0' ALT="Send New Private Message"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=112&t=001027&reply_num=000005&u=00000997"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=112&t=001027&replyto=000005"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
When you take an item off of an "equipped" slot and put it into a trade window, the item does NOT go back to the appropriate body slot when the trade is cancelled.  It goes into an open inventory slot, which can be either a spot in a container (like a backpack) or one of your 8 container slots.<P>If you have 8 bags and put 4 in a trade window, then add 4 equipped items to the trade window and cancel the trade, you'll have 8 items (4 bags and 4 others) competing for 4 open inventory slots.  If the single items go into the inventory slots first, then there's no room for the bags and they hit the ground.  If the bags go in first, then the equipped items try to find room somewhere in one of the bags.  If there's no room in the bags, then they hit the ground.  Chances are you're going to lose something.<P>Keep in mind that this game is played by a lot of pre-teens and older adolescents.  These people often have no sense of fair play, very little guilt, and enjoy breaking whatever rules they can find.  The fact that there are few (if any) repercussions to their act just makes it all the more attractive to them.  When I see a cheat or a scam I call it out to the zone immediately.  I let everyone know what the scammer is up to and I am absolutely merciless about it.  Verant are the judges, which means we have to be the cops.<P>Tips for trading -<BR> - Don't use a bag in trade unless you're prepared to lose everything that's in it if you go LD<BR> - Avoid three-way exchanges; whenever you give something away make sure you are getting what you want IN THAT TRADE<BR> - Just prior to hitting the TRADE button, inspect everything you give as well as everything you get; if someone comes back to you and says you gave them the wrong thing you can tell them "No, I did not".  End of discussion.<BR> - If someone seems like they're in a hurry to make the deal then be extra careful.  Let's say you put three items up and they put their items up and they hit TRADE immediately; they're either very naive or they're bent.  The fact that they didn't inspect what they're getting should make you suspicious about what they're giving you.<BR> - Try not to deal with level 5 mules.<BR> - Try to deal with folks who have guild tags that you recognize.<BR> - Make a receipt for big transactions or whenver you have to do a 3-way deal; type "%t, I am trading you <item_a> for <item_b>.  Is this correct?  If so, say 'yes'."  When they respond, you have an automatic report and petition ready to go if they try to scam you later.<P>Izzy
</FONT>
